com.github.naoghuman.lib.tag.core

Interface TagRelationContainerId

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultTagRelationContainerId

    public interface TagRelationContainerId
    This Interface contains the default method generateId(Class, Class, String) which allowed the developer to generate an unique Id and returned it as a String.

    The main point from this Interface is the possibility to generate an unique Id for a relation between a Tag and the container where the Tag will be embbeded.

    For additional information about the relation plz see TagRelationBuilder.

    Since:
    0.3.0
    Version:
    0.4.0
    Author:
    Naoghuman
    See Also:
    Tag, TagRelation, TagRelationBuilder

    • Method Summary

      String generateId(Class path, Class container, String containerId)

    • Method Detail

      • generateId

        String generateId(Class path,
                  Class container,
                  String containerId)
        Generates an (unique) Id as an String. The format from the Id is:
        • path.getCanonicalName() + '_' + container.getSimpleName() + '_' + containerId
        Example:
        • com.github.naoghuman.lib.tag.internal.DefaultIdGeneratorTest_AnchorPane_832531206890821
        Internal DefaultTagValidator will be used to validate if path, container and containerId isn't NULL. The parameter containerId will be checked additional if it isn't EMPTY.
        Parameters:
        path - usually the path from the class where the Tag used.
        container - usually the type of the container where the Tag should be embbeded.
        containerId - the Id from the container.
        Returns:
        the generated Id.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the containerId is EMPTY.
        NullPointerException - if path, container or containerId is NULL.
        Since:
        0.3.0
        See Also:
        DefaultTagValidator, System.nanoTime()
